The paper discusses the application of convex duality to reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on policy evaluation and optimization, which are subfields of reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as they are also related to machine learning. The paper also discusses control systems (cs.SY) and neural networks (cs.NE), which are relevant subfields of reinforcement learning, but to a lesser extent.
